sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS approved_change_count
FROM term_changes
WHERE status = 'approved';

external_knowledge:
- "Medical terms" are specific labels or identifiers used in healthcare to describe diseases, conditions, and other medical concepts;
- "Latest changes" refer to the most recent updates or modifications to these terms;
- "Users" are individuals who have the authority to make changes to the medical terms in the system;
- "Change types" describe the nature of the modifications, such as updates to term labels or descriptions.

- "petals" metaphorically refers to medical terms;
- "pruned" metaphorically refers to reviewed;
- "top 3 freshest" refers to the three most recently reviewed terms in each category.

- "touched by the hands of change" refers to terms that have been modified;
- "guardians of these transformations" refers to the users who made the changes;
- "frequency of changes" refers to the count of changes;
- "recency of the last change" refers to the most recent change date.

